<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-661-064  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 661 064.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  July 23 1990 v24 n30 p4(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Frodo Baggins: rising from the dead. (concerns about the 4096computer virus)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Alexander, Michael.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The computer software security community braces for an invasion bythe so-called 4096 virus.andP;  The 4096 is a particularly destructivecomputer virus that is so-named because it contains 4,096 bytes ofcode.andP;  First discovered in Israel in Nov 1989, the virus is set toactivate on Sep 22, 1990.andP;  It announces its presence in a systemby displaying the message 'Frodo Lives.' This in in reference tothe birthdate of Frodo Baggins, the protagonist in The Lord of theRings trilogy by JRR Tolkien.andP;  According to experts from RG VirusSoftware Systems and the Computer Virus Industry Assn, the virususes a kind of 'stealth' technology to invade a system and wipeout files from the hard disk or prevent the computer from'booting.' Industry experts say that the virus was written bypersons with a detailed knowledge of the MSDOS operating system.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   RG Software Systems Inc. (research).andO;Topic:     Computer virusesComputer security industryForecastingComputer Virus Industry Association.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>